"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997679","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-06","<p>The Government is committed to driving up housing supply where homes are most needed and in March 2016 established the independent Thames Estuary 2050 Growth Commission to develop an ambitious vision and delivery plan for north Kent, south Essex and east London up to 2050.</p><p>The Commission has now produced its report. Government will respond in full to the Commission’s report by the end of the calendar year.</p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-11-06T11:14:52.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997679/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997679/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-30","Housing: Thames Estuary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what recent assessment he has made of the need for investment in housing in the Thames Estuary.","false","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","Bexleyheath and Crayford","Sir David Evennett","185534"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997680","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-05","<p>The UK and Bahrain enjoy an open dialogue where we are able to discuss a range of issues, including human rights.</p><p>During my visit to Bahrain 26-28 October I had a range of bilateral meetings with Bahraini interlocutors and covered many issues, including human rights.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-05T13:27:02.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997680/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997680/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-30","Bahrain: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his Bahraini counterpart on human rights violations in that country; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Dame Louise Ellman","185530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997681","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-05","<p>The information requested could only be provided at a disproportionate cost. However, over this spending review period we have allocated over £1.2 billion in funding to reduce homelessness and rough sleeping, as well as supporting the implementation of the Homelessness Reduction Act. This includes:</p><ul><li>£316 million of core funding to local authorities;</li><li>£215 million of central Government funding for homelessness programmes, which includes £28 million for our Housing First pilots and the £20 million Private Rented Sector Access Fund announced at Autumn Budget 2017;</li><li>£100 million to deliver low-cost ‘move-on’ accommodation places, for people leaving hostels and refuges to make a sustainable recovery; and</li><li>£617 million in Flexible Homelessness Support Grant funding which gives local authorities greater flexibility to prioritise homelessness prevention in their areas.</li></ul>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2018-11-05T15:55:25.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997681/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997681/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997681/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-30","Homelessness: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how much his Department has spent on homelessness programmes (a) in total and (b) by programme in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","185504"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997682","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-06","<p>The Government will respond in full to the report of the Thames Estuary 2050 Growth Commission by the end of the calendar year.</p><p>At Budget 2018 we announced that, drawing on the Thames Estuary Commission report, the government will be supporting a study to develop options and consult the local area on a Great Thames Park.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-11-06T11:23:07.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997682/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997682/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997682/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-30","Thames Estuary 2050 Growth Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, when the Government plans to respond to the report of the Thames Estuary 2050 Growth Commission; what plans he has to implement the recommendations of that Commission; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","Bexleyheath and Crayford","Sir David Evennett","185535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997683","Department for International Trade","false","2018-11-07","<p>We have been in constant dialogue with all our trading partners to achieve continuity by replicating the effects of our existing EU trade agreements. They understand this must be primary objective, and securing continuity will be a strong foundation to build on our already successful trading relationship.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery","185694 ; 185695 ; 185696 ; 185697 ; 185698 ; 185699 ; 185700 ; 185701 ; 185702 ; 185703 ; 185704 ; 185705 ; 185706 ; 185707 ; 185708 ; 185709 ; 185710 ; 185711 ; 185712","2018-11-07T12:17:30.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997683/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997683/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997683/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-10-30","Trade Agreements: Mexico","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what progress he has made in transitioning the existing EU trade agreement with Mexico; and whether he has received any requests for changes to that agreement.","false","Biography information for Antoinette Sandbach","Eddisbury","Antoinette Sandbach","185693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997684","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-05","<p>Providers are responsible for ordering flu vaccines for adults. This winter those aged 65 and over are being offered a newly licenced adjuvanted trivalvent influenza vaccine, Fluad which is intended to offer better protection to this age group. Manufacturer deliveries are being staggered from September to November which may result in some temporary local shortages. A quadrivalent influenza vaccine is recommended for adults aged 18 to 64. There currently remains a surplus of vaccine available to be ordered from manufacturers at a national level. We do not hold specific information on Gloucestershire.</p><p> </p><p>For children, Public Health England procures the vaccine centrally with eligible children. Stocks are carefully managed to ensure there is sufficient and equitable distribution across England.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-11-05T15:35:48.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997684/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997684/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997684/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-30","Influenza: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent assessment he has made of the adequacy of supply of the flu vaccine for (a) people aged over 65 and (b) in general in (i) England and (ii) Gloucestershire; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","185488"
