"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997826","Wales Office","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Office of the Secretary of State for Wales currently has three apprentices working in the Department.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Eastleigh","Mims Davies",,"2018-11-05T11:06:39.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997826/answer","Biography information for Mims Davies","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997826/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997826/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-10-30","Wales Office: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many apprentices are employed in his Department.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","185792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997827","Scotland Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>The Office of the Secretary of Scotland does not employ staff directly. All staff that join do so on assignment, loan or secondment from other government bodies, principally the Ministry of Justice and the Scottish Government, who remain the employers.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","185753 ; 185773","2018-11-06T15:27:36.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997827/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997827/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997827/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-10-30","Scotland Office: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many apprentices are employed in his Department.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","185793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997828","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-11-01","<p>I can confirm there are currently two apprentices employed in the Northern Ireland Office.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-11-01T15:46:05.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997828/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997828/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-10-30","Northern Ireland Office: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many apprentices are employed in his Department.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","185794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997829","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-11-07","<p>The Ministry of Justice currently has 390 members of staff undertaking an apprenticeship programme.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-11-07T17:15:17.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997829/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997829/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-10-30","Ministry of Justice: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many apprentices are employed in his Department.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","185795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997830","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-05","<p>38 apprentices are employed by the Department as of 31 October 2018.</p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-11-05T15:47:52.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997830/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997830/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997830/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-30","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many apprentices are employed in his Department.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","185796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997831","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-05","<p>Public and private sector providers of laser eye surgery are required by law to register with the Care Quality Commission (CQC) for regulation and doctors in the United Kingdom are required to register with the General Medical Council (GMC). The CQC and the GMC have a range of powers for addressing failures in care.</p><p> </p><p>Providers are also expected to follow the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guidelines on photorefractive (laser) surgery. The CQC, NICE and the Royal College of Ophthalmologists are all clear that the risks and complications of such procedures should be discussed with patients beforehand.</p><p> </p><p>No estimate has been made of the number of people experiencing long-term side effects as a result of laser eye surgery because this data is not held centrally.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","185690 ; 185691","2018-11-05T11:08:07.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997831/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997831/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-30","Eyesight: Surgery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that there are means of recourse against private sector providers for patients experiencing long-term side effects as a result of laser eye surgery performed by private providers.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","185689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997832","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-05","<p>The FCO provides consular assistance to British Nationals overseas. We do not normally offer consular assistance to dual British nationals who are in the country of their other nationality unless we consider that the individual is vulnerable and we have humanitarian concerns.</p><p>Our travel advice to Cameroon is kept under constant review. The promotion and protection of human rights in Cameroon remains an objective of the British Government and we remain concerned by the situation in the Anglophone regions. It is vital that urgent steps are taken to reduce the violence and create a meaningful process of national dialogue to address the core issues.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-11-05T13:29:55.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997832/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997832/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-30","Cameroon: Diplomatic Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what consular support his Department is offering to civilians in (a) Cameroon and (b) the Anglophone Region of Cameroon.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","185623"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997833","Cabinet Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>The Government Digital Service (GDS) currently has 45 off payroll (interim) workers in addition to the 751 employees outlined in the previous response.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-11-06T15:10:24.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997833/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997833/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997833/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-10-30","Government Digital Service: Conditions of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 29 October 2018 to Question 183247 on Government Digital Service: Staff, how many of the 751 people employed by the Government Digital Service are off payroll workers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","185524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997834","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>We want and expect to see cross-Channel trade continue to move as freely as possible but it is right that we also consider a range of contingency plans to deal with any disruption. It would be premature, at this stage, to rule out any possible mechanism.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-06T11:59:41.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997834/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997834/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Ferries: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his policy is on his Department chartering commercial roll-on roll-off ferries on the international market for operation between UK and European Union ports after 29 March 2019.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185570"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997835","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>DfT is directly responsible for 17 work streams relating to the UK’s exit from the EU and works with other Government Departments as required to ensure their success. In the most recent reporting submission to DExEU, all 17 of the negotiated and 15 of the contingency work streams are on track to be delivered on time.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-06T11:40:46.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997835/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997835/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997835/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Department for Transport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress has been made on each of the work streams related to the UK leaving the EU for which his Department has (a) responsibility and (b) joint-responsibility with other Government Departments.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997836","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>The information requested is not held by the department.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-06T12:11:57.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997836/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997836/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997836/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Ferries: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will estimate the average (a) hourly pay rate and (b) tour of duty for (i) Ratings and (ii) Officers working in the European roll-on roll-off ferry industry.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185572"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997837","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Five Year Forward View for Mental Health is at the heart of Government plans to transform mental health services and a key part of this is ensuring a reduction in waiting times for key services.</p><p> </p><p>Following publication of the Five Year Forward View, the Government agreed the following waiting times and access targets with NHS England to be achieved by 2020/21:</p><p> </p><p>- For accessing ‘Improving Access to Psychological Therapies’ services 75% of referrals should be seen within six weeks and 95% should be seen within 18 weeks;</p><p>- For eating disorder services 95% of referrals should be seen within four weeks for routine cases and 95% of urgent referrals should be seen within one week; and</p><p>- For the Early Intervention in Psychosis programme 50% of people experiencing a first episode of psychosis should start a National Institute for Health and Care Excellence recommended package of care within two weeks of referral, rising to 60%.</p><p> </p><p>We are on track to meet these targets, which are tracked on the Five Year Forward View dashboard. The Five Year Forward View can be accessed at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Mental-Health-Taskforce-FYFV-final.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/Mental-Health-Taskforce-FYFV-final.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The dashboard can be accessed at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/publication/mental-health-five-year-forward-view-dashboard/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/publication/mental-health-five-year-forward-view-dashboard/</a></p><p> </p><p>The Government announced its long term financial settlement for the National Health Service in June. This will represent an increase of £20.5 billion by 2023/24. The Government has asked NHS England to develop a long term plan by the end of the year.</p><p> </p><p>The 2018 Budget set out some of aspects of what the long term plan will contain, and further details will follow when the plan is published in due course.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-11-05T15:44:09.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997837/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997837/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997837/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-30","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to reduce waiting times for patients in need of mental health treatment.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","185692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997838","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>I have made no such estimate or assessment.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-06T12:04:21.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997838/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997838/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997838/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Ferries: Calais","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the (a) cost and (b) number of merchant seafarers that would be required to crew ten roll-on roll-off ferries to operate between Dover and Calais for one year from 29 March 2019; and what assessment he has made of whether that demand could be met by current numbers of qualified UK (i) Ratings and (ii) Officers.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185573"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997839","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>Capacity in the international roll-on roll-off commercial ferry market, particularly in relation to ferries capable of operating North Sea routes at short notice, is relatively limited. This is one of the reasons why we are preparing various contingencies in the unlikely event of a no-deal scenario.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-06T11:44:37.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997839/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997839/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997839/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Ferries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when his Department last analysed capacity in the international roll-on roll-off commercial ferry market; and if he will publish the results of that analysis.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997840","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>The proportion of total tonnage handled by UK major ports in each year from 2010 to 2017 that was roll-on roll-off freight is displayed in the table below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Roll-on Roll-off freight as a proportion of tonnage handled at all UK major ports</p></td><td><p>19%</p></td><td><p>19%</p></td><td><p>19%</p></td><td><p>19%</p></td><td><p>20%</p></td><td><p>21%</p></td><td><p>23%</p></td><td><p>23%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Table PORT0201 available here <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/port-and-domestic-waterborne-freight-statistics-port" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/port-and-domestic-waterborne-freight-statistics-port</a></p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-06T16:19:56.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997840/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997840/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Ferries: Freight","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport,  what proportion of the total tonnage handled at UK ports in each year since 2010 was roll-on roll-off freight.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185575"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997841","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>To verify an exhaustive listing of such ports would entail disproportionate cost. However, in 2017 the following UK ports handled substantial volumes of ro-ro ferry units, including domestic traffic:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Dover</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Grimsby &amp; Immingham</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Liverpool</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Holyhead</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Belfast</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Harwich</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Heysham</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Felixstowe</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Portsmouth</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cairnryan</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Larne</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Loch Ryan</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hull</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Teesport</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Warrenpoint</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Milford Haven</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Newhaven</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fishguard</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aberdeen</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Poole</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Forth</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tyne</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Orkney</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Southampton</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Plymouth</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bristol</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-06T11:23:43.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997841/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997841/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997841/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Ferries: Freight","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will list the UK ports with the infrastructure required to handle roll-on roll-off ferry freight units.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185576"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997842","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>My Department and its predecessor departments have not chartered a commercial ro-ro ferry on the international market in recent times.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-06T11:47:57.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997842/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997842/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997842/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Ferries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when his Department or predecessor Departments last chartered a roll-on roll-off commercial ferry on the international market; and what the cost of that contract to the public purse was in today’s prices.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185577"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997843","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>The number of merchant roll-on-roll off ferries that are currently registered on Red Ensign Group shipping registers is 120; there are 112 on the United Kingdom register, five on the Isle of Man register and one each on the registers of Bermuda, the Cayman Islands and the British Virgin Islands.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-06T12:07:28.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997843/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997843/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997843/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Roll-on Roll-off Ships: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many merchant roll-on roll-off ferries are currently registered on Red Ensign Group shipping registers.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997844","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>I have made no such estimate of the number of merchant roll-on roll-off ferries in the international shipping industry that are owned by UK shipowners.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-06T11:26:29.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997844/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997844/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997844/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Ferries: Ownership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the number of merchant roll-on roll-off ferries in the international shipping industry that are owned by UK shipowners.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997845","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-07","<p>Inter-Ministerial Group meetings have not included, and would not normally include, such attendance. Officials meet with shipping companies on a regular basis.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2018-11-07T11:26:28.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997845/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997845/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Shipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will list the (a) shipping companies and (b) shipowner representatives that have attended meetings of the EU Exit Inter-Ministerial Groups with Ministers or officials from his Department.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997846","Department for International Development","false","2018-11-06","<p>There are currently over 368,000 refugees in Cameroon from conflicts in North East Nigeria and the Central African Republic. We are providing £6.55 million in humanitarian support to Cameroon this year, including for protection, nutrition, health, food security and livelihoods to support these refugees and those internally displaced in the north of Cameroon.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-11-06T15:29:44.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997846/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997846/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-10-30","Cameroon: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is providing to refugees in Cameroon.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","185624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997847","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-06","<p>Estimates of UK officers active at sea from 1997 to 2001 are shown in the table</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Number of UK certificated officers active at sea, assuming retirement at age 62</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1997</p></td><td><p>14,300</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1998</p></td><td><p>13,550</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1999</p></td><td><p>13,300</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2000</p></td><td><p>12,510</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2001</p></td><td><p>12,300</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Equivalent estimates for ratings are not available.</p><p> </p><p>The figures above were previously published as part of the annual seafarer statistics series and will be added when the 2018 statistics are published.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-11-06T11:56:26.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997847/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997847/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Merchant Shipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many UK merchant navy (a) Ratings and (b) Officers were working at sea in 1997; and if he will ensure that the annual UK Seafarer Statistics is extended to include the relevant statistics for the period from 1997 to 2001.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","185581"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997848","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-12","<p>This information is not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost. At Autumn Budget, the Housing Infrastructure Fund was increased by £500 million to a total of £5.5 billion.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2018-11-12T17:07:05.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997848/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997848/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997848/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-30","Housing Infrastructure Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how much his Department has spent on grant funding for infrastructure associated with housing developments in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","185514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997849","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-05","<p>Public and private sector providers of laser eye surgery are required by law to register with the Care Quality Commission (CQC) for regulation and doctors in the United Kingdom are required to register with the General Medical Council (GMC). The CQC and the GMC have a range of powers for addressing failures in care.</p><p> </p><p>Providers are also expected to follow the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guidelines on photorefractive (laser) surgery. The CQC, NICE and the Royal College of Ophthalmologists are all clear that the risks and complications of such procedures should be discussed with patients beforehand.</p><p> </p><p>No estimate has been made of the number of people experiencing long-term side effects as a result of laser eye surgery because this data is not held centrally.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","185689 ; 185691","2018-11-05T11:08:07.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997849/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997849/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-30","Eyesight: Surgery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that providers of laser eye surgery clearly outline the risks of that procedure to patients prior to such surgery taking place.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","185690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997850","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-05","<p>Public and private sector providers of laser eye surgery are required by law to register with the Care Quality Commission (CQC) for regulation and doctors in the United Kingdom are required to register with the General Medical Council (GMC). The CQC and the GMC have a range of powers for addressing failures in care.</p><p> </p><p>Providers are also expected to follow the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guidelines on photorefractive (laser) surgery. The CQC, NICE and the Royal College of Ophthalmologists are all clear that the risks and complications of such procedures should be discussed with patients beforehand.</p><p> </p><p>No estimate has been made of the number of people experiencing long-term side effects as a result of laser eye surgery because this data is not held centrally.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","185689 ; 185690","2018-11-05T11:08:07.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997850/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997850/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-30","Eyesight: Surgery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate his Department has made of the number of people experiencing long-term side effects as a result of laser eye surgery.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","185691"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997851","Treasury","false","2018-11-05","<p>To date more than 391,000 parents have opened a Tax–Free Childcare account and over 109,000 parents have used their account to make a payment to a childcare provider.</p><p> </p><p>Around 313,000 of the parents who have opened a Tax-Free Childcare account applied at the same time as for 30 hours free childcare. 30 hours free childcare saves parents using the full 30 hours up to £5,000 per child per year.</p><p> </p><p>Tax-Free Childcare account usage is substantially higher amongst parents who get Tax-Free Childcare only, compared to parents who have both a Tax-Free Childcare and 30 hours free childcare account.</p><p> </p><p>8,265 Tax-Free Childcare accounts have been closed since the scheme launched in April 2017.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","185723","2018-11-05T16:34:52.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997851/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997851/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-10-30","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many tax-free childcare accounts have (a) been created and (b) had at least one payment made from that account to date.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","185722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997852","Treasury","false","2018-11-05","<p>To date more than 391,000 parents have opened a Tax–Free Childcare account and over 109,000 parents have used their account to make a payment to a childcare provider.</p><p> </p><p>Around 313,000 of the parents who have opened a Tax-Free Childcare account applied at the same time as for 30 hours free childcare. 30 hours free childcare saves parents using the full 30 hours up to £5,000 per child per year.</p><p> </p><p>Tax-Free Childcare account usage is substantially higher amongst parents who get Tax-Free Childcare only, compared to parents who have both a Tax-Free Childcare and 30 hours free childcare account.</p><p> </p><p>8,265 Tax-Free Childcare accounts have been closed since the scheme launched in April 2017.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","185722","2018-11-05T16:34:52.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997852/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997852/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997852/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-10-30","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many parents have closed a tax-free childcare account since that policy was introduced.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","185723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997853","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-07","<p>The Homes England Strategic Plan 2018 to 2023 sets out the agreed budget for 2018/19 and provisional budgets for future years to 31 March 2021. Following the Chancellor's recent Budget, the Department is working through the 2018/19 Supplementary Estimates process to align budget profiles with delivery plans. Updated budgetary information will be published once the Supplementary Estimates process has concluded. Budgets beyond 2020/21 will be agreed through the forthcoming Spending Review.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2018-11-07T11:46:17.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997853/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997853/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997853/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-30","Homes England: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will provide a breakdown by financial year of the allocations in Homes England's financial plan set out in strategic plan 2018-19 – 2022-23.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","185515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997854","Home Office","false","2018-11-05","<p><br>We do not have specific information about children under 10 years of age involved in county lines. However, the Home Office has commissioned regular threat assessments of county lines by the National Crime Agency, which provide the most detailed and reliable intelligence on the scale and nature of county lines.</p><p>The threat assessments do not contain estimates of the number of children involved due to data limitations but they report that the threat has grown. The NCA is currently preparing a new threat assessment for publication shortly.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","185473 ; 185475","2018-11-05T17:42:52.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997854/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997854/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-30","Organised Crime: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether his Department holds information on trends in the number of children below the minimum age of criminal responsibility involved in county lines activity.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","185472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997855","Home Office","false","2018-11-05","<p><br>We do not have specific information about children under 10 years of age involved in county lines. However, the Home Office has commissioned regular threat assessments of county lines by the National Crime Agency, which provide the most detailed and reliable intelligence on the scale and nature of county lines.</p><p>The threat assessments do not contain estimates of the number of children involved due to data limitations but they report that the threat has grown. The NCA is currently preparing a new threat assessment for publication shortly.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","185472 ; 185475","2018-11-05T17:42:52.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997855/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997855/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997855/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-30","Organised Crime: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate his Department has made of the number of children below the minimum age of criminal responsibility who were involved in county lines activity in (a) 2015, (b) 2016 and (c) 2017.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","185473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997856","Department for Education","false","2018-11-05","<p>My right hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Education has visited, since his appointment on 8 January 2018, five nurseries, and has spent time meeting nursery children and teachers during four primary school visits. He has not yet visited any childminders.</p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-11-05T14:46:57.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997856/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997856/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997856/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-10-30","Primary Education: Nurseries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many (a) nurseries, (b) childminders and (c) nursery classes based in primary schools he has visited since his appointment.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","185724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997857","Home Office","false","2019-03-05","<p>We do not provide specific support services to children under 10 involved in county lines activity. However the Government provides a range of support for county lines victims including: funding Young People’s Advocates in Birmingham, Manchester and London; funding through the Trusted Relationships fund of £13 million over two years to help foster relationships between frontline professionals and young people at risk of exploitation including county lines; publication of guidance for frontline professionals on how to identify potential victims of county lines and the appropriate referral routes; £17.7 million over two years through the Early Intervention Youth Fund to help deliver services to support and prevent young people from getting involved in crime, including county lines. The funds are not restricted by the age of criminal responsibility.</p><p>Criminally exploited children who have also been trafficked are identified and supported through the National Referral Mechanism, which can include support from Independent Child Trafficking Advocates which we have committed to rolling out nationally.</p><p>The Department for Education has also just announced £2 million for a new national response unit that will be established to help local authorities support vulnerable children at risk of exploitation.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-03-05T16:35:05.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997857/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997857/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997857/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-30","Drugs: Organised Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what support his Department provides to children below the minimum age of criminal responsibility who (a) are or (b) have been involved in county lines activity.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","185474"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997858","Home Office","false","2018-11-05","<p><br>We do not have specific information about children under 10 years of age involved in county lines. However, the Home Office has commissioned regular threat assessments of county lines by the National Crime Agency, which provide the most detailed and reliable intelligence on the scale and nature of county lines.</p><p>The threat assessments do not contain estimates of the number of children involved due to data limitations but they report that the threat has grown. The NCA is currently preparing a new threat assessment for publication shortly.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","185472 ; 185473","2018-11-05T17:42:52.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997858/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997858/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997858/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-30","Organised Crime: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate his Department has made of the number of children below the minimum age of criminal responsibility involved in county lines activity who were referred to a pupil referral unit in (a) 2015, (b) 2016 and (c) 2017.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","185475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997859","Department for Education","false","2018-11-05","<p>The number of employment-based early years trainees for whom the department provided early years initial teacher training (ITT) funding in academic years 2016/17 and 2017/18 is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Academic year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of early years ITT trainees</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>451</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017/18</p></td><td><p>431</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>For all trainees shown above, both the training grant and employer incentive was provided.</p><p>We are unable to provide any data collected prior to the academic year 2016/17. A review of early years ITT data found that prior to the academic year 2016/17, data was not collected with sufficient quality to produce high quality statistics.</p><p> </p><p>Further information about this and the subsequent actions put in place by the department, can be found in the ‘Data collection and quality’ section of the ITT Census 2017/18, found here at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2017-to-2018</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-11-05T14:31:32.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997859/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997859/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997859/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-10-30","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many graduates in paid employment in an early years setting who undertake training to achieve the Teachers’ Standards (Early Years) have accessed (a) grant funding, (b) employer incentive and (c) both grant funding and employer incentive in each year since that policy was introduced.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","185725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997860","Department for Education","false","2018-11-05","<p>We do not centrally collect the data requested.</p><p> </p><p>However, the number of workers with qualifications at various levels is published in our ‘Childcare and early years providers surveys’ at: <br> <br> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/childcare-and-early-years-providers-survey-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/childcare-and-early-years-providers-survey-2016</a>.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/childcare-and-early-years-providers-survey-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/childcare-and-early-years-providers-survey-2013</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The 2018 survey is due to be published on 1 November 2018.</p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-11-05T12:47:18.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997860/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997860/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997860/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-10-30","Teachers: Qualifications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many individuals employed in early years settings have achieved level 3 qualifications in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","185726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997861","Home Office","false","2018-11-07","<p>The current number of apprentices in employment at the Home Office and undertaking an apprenticeship is 348.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-11-07T15:00:10.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997861/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997861/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997861/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-30","Home Office: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many apprentices are employed in his Department.","false","Biography information for David Linden","Glasgow East","David Linden","185797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997862","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>​The UK remains firmly committed to the full implementation of UN Human Rights Council Resolution 34/1, under which Sri Lanka committed to implement a range of measures to provide for human rights, truth-seeking and reconciliation following the end of its civil war. I encouraged Foreign Minister Marapana, officials and others to continue to make progress on these commitments when I visited Colombo in the first week of October 2018. Our High Commission in Sri Lanka regularly travel to the North and East and meet with local groups, and where we have specific human rights concerns we raise these with the Sri Lankan government.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-06T11:19:54.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997862/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997862/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997862/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-30","Sri Lanka: Tamils","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions  he has had with his Sri Lankan counterpart on the status of Tamil people.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","185496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997863","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>​We have not recently discussed the status of Tamil people in Sri Lanka with the Secretary General of the Commonwealth. However, we welcomed her visit to Colombo in August, during which she offered Commonwealth support on good governance and accountability.</p><p>The UK is committed to supporting human rights and reconciliation for all Sri Lankans. While we welcome some recent progress against its UN Human Rights Council commitments, more remains to be done. I visited Colombo in October where I urged the government to make more progress, including towards the establishment of transitional justice and accountability mechanisms; devolution through constitutional reform; and the repeal of the Prevention of Terrorism Act. I also met Tamil National Alliance leader and human rights and civil society activists. In August we announced £1 million of extra UK funding to support resettlement of war-displaced families in the predominantly Tamil north and east. Total UK funding is now £7.9 million for 2016-2019.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-06T11:52:01.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997863/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997863/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997863/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-30","Sri Lanka: Tamils","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with the Deputy General of the Commonwealth on the status of Tamil people in Sri Lanka.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","185497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997864","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>​I have not had recent discussions with President Sirisena. However, in my visit to Colombo in early October I encouraged Foreign Minister Marapana, officials and others to continue to make progress on Sri Lanka's human rights and reconciliation commitments when I visited Colombo in October 2018.</p><p>Our High Commissioner met with President Sirisena on 1 November to raise our concerns at recent political developments.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-06T11:22:43.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997864/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997864/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997864/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-30","Sri Lanka: Tamils","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the President of Sri Lanka on the security of Tamil communities in that country.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","185498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997865","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Ministry of Defence is committed to providing high quality services to our veterans and their families and we are continually looking for ways to improve these services. The Future Service Delivery Contract (FSDC) competition was launched on 6 April 2018 to re-compete the currently outsourced contract for the delivery of military pay, pensions and administration of personnel records which expires in November 2019.</p><p>Included in the scope of the project is the market testing of some areas that are not currently outsourced, including some elements of veterans services; the Armed Forces Compensation Schemes and the War Pensions Schemes (and their associated support services). Their inclusion for market testing in no way indicates that the outcome will be the addition of these services to the already outsourced contract. However, we owe it to taxpayers and our serving military and veterans to explore whether the market can deliver increased value for money and more up to date digital enhancements to improve the efficiency and quality of the services. We also need to be sure that the current in-house delivery is still providing the best value and quality for Defence.</p><p>The FSDC Project has regularly engaged with Trades Unions and stakeholders across Defence. Formal TU Consultation will take place at the appropriate time, should the market testing show that an external provider could provide better value for money.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-11-05T17:02:21.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997865/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997865/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997865/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-30","Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what consultations his Department has conducted on the proposed outsourcing of veteran services; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","185637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997866","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-05","<p>The UK Shared Prosperity Fund (UKSPF) will be a new fund which affords a fresh opportunity to spend money according to our own priorities rather than those set by the EU.</p><p>We want to ensure that the UKSPF is designed to support rural economies and communities.</p><p>We intend to consult on the design and priorities of the UKSPF later this year. This will inform decisions on the operation and allocations of the Fund which will be taken as part of the 2019 Spending Review.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-11-05T15:56:46.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997866/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997866/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997866/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-30","UK Shared Prosperity Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of providing Pillar 2 CAP funding for England through the proposed UK Shared Prosperity Fund after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","185737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997867","Home Office","false","2018-11-05","<p>There has been no formal consultation relating to collective passports in the last 12 months. We continually review all of our services, and engage with relevant stakeholders as appropriate<br>The collective passport remains available for those who require it.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-11-05T17:03:25.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997867/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997867/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997867/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-30","Passports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what consultations his Department has conducted on the future of the HMPO collective passports service in the last 12 months; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","185638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997868","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Secretary of State has been to the Scottish Parliament twice and had quarterly meetings with the Scottish Government. Over the summer the Secretary of State visited 4 Scottish jobcentres, engaging with a variety of Scottish organisations and staff in these offices. There is not a further visit planned to Scotland this November.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-11-05T15:37:28.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997868/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997868/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997868/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-10-30","Jobcentres: Glasgow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether she plans to visit Govan job centre in November 2018; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","185639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997869","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>​I am concerned by the fast developing political situation in Sri Lanka. I have called on all parties to ensure that the constitution is respected and due political and legal process upheld. I urge the President, in consultation with the Speaker, to reconvene parliament immediately to give the democratically elected representatives of the Sri Lankan people their voice. The UK will continue to urge Sri Lanka to implement fully the commitments it made to the UN Human Rights Council.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-06T11:24:40.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997869/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997869/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997869/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-30","Sri Lanka: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the political situation in Sri Lanka.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","185499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997870","Treasury","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Budget showed how the hard work of the British people is paying off. Our balanced approach means that our public finances have reached a turning point and austerity is coming to an end. We are providing more support for our vital public services like the NHS, cutting income tax for 32 million people and investing for the long term to boost growth and deliver higher living standards, while remaining committed to fiscal discipline.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-11-05T17:02:14.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997870/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997870/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997870/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-10-30","Public Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 29 October to Question 183422 on Public Finance and with reference to his financial statement of 29 October 2018, if he will provide a formal definition of the word austerity; and by what methodology his Department measures austerity in public policy.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","185532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997871","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-11-05","<p>In line with requirements under the Trade Union Act 2016, the Department will arrange a roundtable to consult the relevant organisations and professionals on Sir Ken Knight’s report on his review of electronic balloting for industrial action. Invitees will be drawn from interested groups, including the trade unions. Following that consultation, we will respond to Sir Ken’s report.</p><p> </p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2018-11-05T16:29:50.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997871/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997871/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997871/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-10-30","Trade Unions: Electronic Voting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when he plans to publish Department's review of trade unions using electronic balloting in future industrial action ballots; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","185640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997872","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>​There have been no recent national elections in Sri Lanka. I am nevertheless concerned by the ongoing political situation and have publicly called for the President, in consultation with the Speaker, to convene the Sri Lankan parliament immediately to give the democratically elected representatives of the Sri Lankan people their voice.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-06T11:26:44.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997872/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997872/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997872/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-30","Sri Lanka: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his department is taking to support an orderly transfer of power in Sri Lanka following the recent elections in that country.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","185500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997873","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Secretary of State has been to the Scottish Parliament twice and had quarterly meetings with the Scottish Government. Over the summer the Secretary of State visited 6 constituencies, engaging with a variety of Scottish organisations and staff in Scottish job centres. There is not a further visit planned to Scotland this November.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2018-11-05T16:10:37.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997873/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997873/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997873/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-10-30","Food Banks: Glasgow South West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if she will visit a food bank in the Glasgow South West constituency in November 2018; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","185641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997874","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-05","<p>Information on National Health Service contracts entered into by NHS England and their local commissioning bodies - clinical commissioning groups - is not held centrally.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","185643","2018-11-05T15:56:12.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997874/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997874/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997874/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-30","NHS: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what proportion of payments for NHS England contracts to third party companies go to companies based outside of the Government’s jurisdiction for corporation tax purposes.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","185642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997875","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-11-05","<p>Information on National Health Service contracts entered into by NHS England and their local commissioning bodies - clinical commissioning groups - is not held centrally.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","185642","2018-11-05T15:56:12.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997875/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997875/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997875/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-30","NHS: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what proportion of NHS England contracts to third party companies go to companies based outside of the Government’s jurisdiction for corporation tax purposes.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","185643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997876","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>​I made statements on 26 and 29 October setting out our concerns at political developments in Sri Lanka and calling for due political process to be upheld. The FCO condems any reported intimidation of journalists and TV stations.</p><p>The UK is committed to supporting human rights and reconciliation for all Sri Lankans. While we welcome some recent progress against its UN Human Rights Council commitments, more remains to be done. I visited Colombo in early October, where I urged the government to make more progress, including towards the establishment of transitional justice and accountability mechanisms; constitutional reform; and the repeal of the Prevention of Terrorism Act (PTA). I also met the leader of the Tamil National Alliance, as well as human rights and civil society activists. In August we announced £1m of extra UK funding to support resettlement of war-displaced families in the north and east of the country.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-06T11:38:35.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997876/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997876/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997876/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-30","Sri Lanka: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to support the protection of human rights in Sri Lanka.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","185501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997877","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>I met Foreign Minister Marapana on the 6 of October 2018 in Colombo.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-11-06T11:54:35.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997877/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997877/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997877/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-30","Sri Lanka: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, on what date did he last spoke with his Sri Lankan counterpart.","false","Biography information for Keith Vaz","Leicester East","Keith Vaz","185502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997878","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Government awarded £14.9 million in the 2014-15 financial year as part of its Building Foundations for Growth Fund. The release of this funding was dependant on the Accountable Body, North Lincolnshire Council, verifying that the site had reached agreed milestones. The Accountable Body confirmed that all conditions for the grant had been met. Further development of ABLE is a commercial matter for the company.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-11-05T15:57:26.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997878/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997878/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997878/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-30","ABLE Humber Port","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 4 June 2018 to Question 146924 on ABLE Humber Port, what steps he is taking to monitor the effect of the Government’s investment in the Able Marine Energy Park.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","185644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997879","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-11-05","<p>On 23 July 2018, the Government announced the timetable for future CfD auctions with the next Pot 2 allocation round opening by the end of May 2019, and then an auction every 2 years. Depending on the price achieved, each CfD round could deliver 1 GW to 2 GW of new offshore wind every year in 2020s. This forward visibility and certainty can help businesses to plan and make the investment decisions they need, to be in a growing global sector, supporting our ambitious Industrial Strategy and helping to develop UK supply chains.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-11-05T09:44:47.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997879/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997879/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-10-30","Humber Estuary: Wind Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 4 June to Question 146924 ABLE Humber Port, what further steps he is taking to support the growth of on-shore wind on the South Bank of the Humber.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","185645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997880","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-11-06","<p>​We understand that Sudan is contributing troops to the Saudi-led coalition in Yemen, though we do not have an assessment of the numbers of troops on the ground or their roles. We continue to urge all sides to engage with the UN-led peace process.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-11-06T17:24:58.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997880/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997880/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997880/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-30","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment has he made of the contribution of the Sudan Defence Force to the conflict in Yemen; and whether he had made representations to his Sudanese counterpart to seek an early withdrawal of those troops.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","185487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997881","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-11-02","<p>Following the publication in 2017 of the National Shipbuilding Strategy Government has established the Maritime Enterprise Working Group (MEWG) to coordinate discussions with industry around growth opportunities. The MEWG has commissioned a market evaluation and competitiveness study of UK Shipbuilding which will report in the New Year. This study will identify a prospective international commercial and naval product mix for UK shipbuilding; analyse market characteristics, prospective clients and competitor strengths and weaknesses. The study will assess the competitiveness and performance levels of UK shipbuilders and will identify actions needed to address any gaps. The Department is supporting this study.</p><p> </p><p>The ability of UK industry to win contracts to build military vessels for EU member states after the UK leaves the EU will remain a decision for EU member states. The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy is working closely with industry and other Government Departments to understand the implications and opportunities presented by the UK's departure from the European Union.</p><p> </p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-11-02T14:38:40.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997881/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997881/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997881/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-10-30","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment the Government has made of the ability of UK shipyards to secure contracts to build military vessels for EU member states after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","185469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997882","House of Commons Commission","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Clerk of the House replied to the letter from the Equality and Human Rights Commission on 23 March 2018. A copy of that reply has already been sent to the Women and Equalities Committee and has been placed in the Library.</p><p>The letter from the Equality and Human Rights Commission listed a number of matters they wished to discuss at a meeting. These were discussed at a meeting on 23 April 2018.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2018-11-05T10:46:15.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997882/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997882/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997882/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2018-10-30","House of Commons: Bullying","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington, representing the House of Commons Commission, with reference to the letter from the Chief Executive of the Equality and Human Rights Commission to the Clerk of the House of 19 March 2018 on Newsnight report into bullying and harassment, if the Commission will publish the response to that letter; and what information was provided to the Equality and Human Rights Commission in response to the questions listed at the end of that letter.","false","Biography information for Mrs Maria Miller","Basingstoke","Mrs Maria Miller","185545"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997883","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-11-02","<p>While the future of Appledore is a matter for Babcock, the Ministry of Defence (MOD) has remained closely engaged with the company on this issue. Together with MOD officials, both the Secretary of State for Defence and I have met Babcock to explore potential options. This included bringing forward a potential £60 million package of work at Devonport, thereby providing additional work for Appledore workers. However, our discussions with Babcock established that this work would not be enough to secure the long-term future of the yard.</p><p>Regrettably, Babcock has now stated that it has reached a point where it can no longer sustain the cost of its operations at Appledore. This is clearly a concerning time for Appledore employees and their families and, while Babcock will offer all those affected other positions, the Government is standing by to provide any additional support.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-11-02T14:53:20.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997883/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997883/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997883/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-30","Appledore Shipyard","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions his Department has held with Babcock on securing the future of Appledore shipyard.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","185470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997884","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-11-05","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy is in close contact with Babcock regarding the closure of Appledore Shipyard. The Department is liaising closely with the MOD who have spent £1.7bn with Babcock last year. The MOD had explored a range of options with Babcock but this was not enough for Babcock to decide to maintain the Appledore facility.. In the event of job losses being announced, the Government will provide assistance through its Rapid Response Service and is ready to support any employee affected by this announcement.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-11-05T16:32:37.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997884/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997884/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/997884/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-10-30","Appledore Shipyard","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions his Department has held with Babcock on securing the future of Appledore shipyard.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","185471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/998457","Department for Transport","false","2018-11-12","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>There are no stations that will be served by Crossrail 1 trains that have a station platform height of 1000mm or 750mm.</p><p> </p><p>The Crossrail rolling stock contract is held and managed by Transport for London (TfL), and therefore any conversations with train manufacturers regarding the specification of the Elizabeth line trains are a matter for TfL. However, Crossrail Limited have provided the Department with a summary of their findings concerning the possible use of trains with floor heights lower than 1100mm. Crossrail Limited identified significant problems that would have impacted upon the design of the train, such as a widening of the gauge profile which would result in unacceptable infringements on gauge clearances at legacy platforms.</p><p> </p><p>As the future operator of the Elizabeth line, the operating costs for stations are a matter for TfL.</p><p>Crossrail 2 is under development. Detailed design requirements including platform heights will be considered as development progresses.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg","HL11117 ; HL11118 ; HL11119","2018-11-12T17:14:55.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/998457/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/998457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/998457/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-30","Crossrail Line","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Sugg on 17 May (HL7494), how many stations to be serviced by Crossrail 1 trains have station platform heights of (1) 1000 mm, and (2) 750mm.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL11116"
